            <title>[JCR-1355] XML import should not access external entities</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1355</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>With current Jackrabbit the following XML document can not be imported:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE foo SYSTEM &amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://invalid.address/&quot;&gt;http://invalid.address/&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;foo/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Even if the DTD address (or some other external resource referenced in the XML document) is correct, I don&amp;#39;t think importXML() should even try resolving those references.</description>
